# Kubernetes Deployment for <%= baseName %>

Generated by [JHipster Rust](https://github.com/pandeyn/generator-jhipster-rust).

> **Recommended:** For production deployments, consider using Helm charts instead of raw manifests. Helm provides parameterized deployments, release tracking, upgrades, and rollback support.
>
> ```bash
> jhipster-rust kubernetes:helm
> ```

## Prerequisites

- [kubectl](https://kubernetes.io/docs/tasks/tools/) configured with cluster access
- [Docker](https://www.docker.com/) for building container images
- A Kubernetes cluster (minikube, kind, EKS, GKE, AKS, etc.)

## Quick Start

### 1. Build the Docker image

```bash
<%_ if (dockerRegistryUrl) { _%>
docker build -t <%= dockerImageName %>:latest .
docker push <%= dockerImageName %>:latest
<%_ } else { _%>
docker build -t <%= baseName.toLowerCase() %>:latest .
# If using minikube: eval $(minikube docker-env) before building
# If using kind: kind load docker-image <%= baseName.toLowerCase() %>:latest
<%_ } _%>
```

### 2. Deploy to Kubernetes

```bash
# Apply all manifests in the correct order
./k8s/kubectl-apply.sh apply

# Or apply manually:
<%_ if (kubernetesNamespace !== 'default') { _%>
kubectl apply -f k8s/namespace.yml
<%_ } _%>
kubectl apply -f k8s/app-secret.yml
kubectl apply -f k8s/app-configmap.yml
<%_ if (devDatabaseTypePostgresql) { _%>
kubectl apply -f k8s/postgresql-statefulset.yml
<%_ } else if (devDatabaseTypeMysql) { _%>
kubectl apply -f k8s/mysql-statefulset.yml
<%_ } else if (devDatabaseTypeMongodb) { _%>
kubectl apply -f k8s/mongodb-statefulset.yml
<%_ } _%>
kubectl apply -f k8s/app-deployment.yml
kubectl apply -f k8s/app-service.yml
<%_ if (ingressEnabled) { _%>
kubectl apply -f k8s/app-ingress.yml
<%_ } _%>
```

### 3. Access the application

```bash
# Port forward to access locally
kubectl port-forward svc/<%= baseName.toLowerCase() %> 8080:8080 -n <%= kubernetesNamespace %>
```

<%_ if (ingressEnabled) { _%>
Or access via Ingress at: `http://<%= baseName.toLowerCase() %>.<%= ingressDomain %>`
<%_ } _%>

