## Customization

### Change secrets

Update `k8s/app-secret.yml` with production-safe values before deploying. Use `stringData` for plain text or `data` with base64 encoded values.

### Scale replicas

```bash
kubectl scale deployment/<%= baseName.toLowerCase() %> --replicas=3 -n <%= kubernetesNamespace %>
```

### TLS/HTTPS

<%_ if (ingressEnabled) { _%>
Uncomment the `tls` section in `k8s/app-ingress.yml` and create a TLS secret:

```bash
kubectl create secret tls <%= baseName.toLowerCase() %>-tls \
  --cert=path/to/cert.pem \
  --key=path/to/key.pem \
  -n <%= kubernetesNamespace %>
```
<%_ } else { _%>
To enable TLS, regenerate with an Ingress controller and configure TLS in the ingress manifest.
<%_ } _%>

## Tear Down

```bash
./k8s/kubectl-apply.sh delete
```

## Upgrading to Helm Charts

For parameterized deployments with `values.yaml` overrides, tracked revisions, and rollback:

```bash
jhipster-rust kubernetes:helm
./helm/helm-apply.sh install
```

See the [Kubernetes Deployment Guide](docs/KUBERNETES.md) for the full comparison.
